messages.message: answering some questions for Citi, and I don’t know the answer to this one:
> Clustering – What is the algorithm used? If proprietary, what’s the base if it can be shared?

(I see it on GH but not sure if it’s nearest neighbors or something else, or if we even disclose:https://github.com/instabase/instabase/blob/77ae0df2f70d350977de51268c348834065e6e15/distributed-tasks/celery/app-tasks/src/py/instabase/tasks/apps/cluster/ngram_cluster.py)
(or can I just call it n-gram clustering?)
IIRC we use an agglomerative method with primarily skip-grams as features, but @Anant would know for sure (I think he implemented it?)
